1535d6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;"> sometimes ask</a> =E2=80=9Cwhy hasn=E2=80=99t Bankman-Frie=
d taken a plea deal?=E2=80=9D Here, for instance, <a href=3D"https://link.m=
ail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32983479.262420/aHR0cHM6Ly9wdWNrLm5ld3Mvcy1=
iLWYtcy1leHBlY3RlZC12YWx1ZS1jYWxjdWxhdGlvbi8/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe451b=
04a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;"> is a claim</a> that Bankman-Fried made a risky bet to go to t=
rial rather than cutting a deal with prosecutors:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CI wonder if it=E2=80=99s =
his insane views on risk. Like, he might just think the E.V. is there and b=
e committed like that,=E2=80=9D one (former) friend said. =E2=80=9CHe might=
 think a 20 percent chance of zero [time] is better than a 100 percent chan=
ce of 20 years.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But the actual answer is much simpler: Bankman=
-Fried didn=E2=80=99t take a plea deal because prosecutors <a href=3D"https=
://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32983479.262420/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYX=
hpb3MuY29tLzIwMjMvMTAvMDMvc2FtLWJhbmttYW4tZnJpZWQtdHJpYWwtZnR4LWNyeXB0bw/60=
7f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBab359be1" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsc=
ope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impo=
rtant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-botto=
m-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> never offered him one</a>, and ne=
ver would. Why would they? They offered plea deals to everyone=C2=A0<em>els=
e=C2=A0</em>in Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s inner circle, to get those people to=
 cooperate and testify against Bankman-Fried, so they can maximize their (<=
a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32983479.262420/aHR=
0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTAtMDIvc2JmLX=
MtZGVmZW5zZS13aWxsLWJlLXRvdWdoP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEwMTAyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZ=
WRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMTAxMCZ1dG1fY2Ft=
cGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd1bd3ede" itemprop=3D"Story=
Link" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">very good=
</a>!) chances of convicting Bankman-Fried. Why would they give <em>him=C2=
=A0</em>a deal? What can he offer them? =E2=80=9CI will testify against <a =
href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32983479.262420/aHR0c=
HM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTAtMDkvc2JmLWZhY2Vz=
