<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meanwhile the prosecutors are making their own=
 fairly straightforward bet:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If they throw the book at him and go =
to trial, they will probably win. The evidence seems strong, they have all =
of his friends testifying against him, and it=E2=80=99s hard for me to imag=
ine a jury saying =E2=80=9Cehh this guy lost $8 billion of customer money b=
ut it was probably just an accident.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D"mar=
gin-bottom: 5px;">If they cut any sort of deal, they will increase their od=
ds of winning from, like, 99% to 100%, but they will get a lot of criticism=
 for going easy on society=E2=80=99s big crypto villain. It=E2=80=99s not w=
orth it! This case is not just about sending Sam Bankman-Fried to prison; i=
t is about explaining what went wrong at FTX, and about saying, with the fu=
ll force of the US government, that That Was Bad. A plea deal doesn=E2=80=
=99t send the right message.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The second bet is: Will Bankman-Fried take the=
 stand and testify in his own defense? Buddy he has <a href=3D"https://link=
.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32983479.262420/aHR0cHM6Ly9zYW1iZi5zdWJzd=
GFjay5jb20vcC9mdHgtcHJlLW1vcnRlbS1vdmVydmlldw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2259=
