tion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0000=
00; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">
screenshots</a> of FTX computer code that is like =E2=80=9CIF you_feel_like=
_it THEN steal(all.the.money).=E2=80=9D His testimony just cannot make thin=
gs worse! The jury is going to get the prosecutors=E2=80=99 story and it is=
 really, really, really, really bad for Bankman-Fried. He needs to tell his=
 side of the story to have any shot at all. If his testimony has a 10% chan=
ce of being compelling and a 90% chance of being disastrous, that is=C2=A0<=
em>all upside</em>.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-4" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; ba=
ckground-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[4]</span>
</a>=C2=A0If he does not testify, that is 100% disastrous.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also, he <em>has </em>charmed people before.=
=C2=A0Obviously the context here is different, and it is easier to be charm=
ed by the world=E2=80=99s youngest self-made billionaire than by a criminal=
 defendant in a fraud trial. But I think the bet, in testifying, has to be =
that Bankman-Fried will sound better and more reasonable in explaining what=
 was going on than the prosecutors will, that they will try to trip him up =
and fail, that he will come across as a reasonable but unlucky nerd and the=
y will come across as unreasonable bullies. I don=E2=80=99t think that is a=
ll that likely, but it is not a=C2=A0<em>crazy=C2=A0</em>bet. And it=E2=80=
=99s better than nothing.</p>
