emscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decor=
ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> writes today</a>=
, the plan was to =E2=80=9Cpull together some of the industry=E2=80=99s big=
gest names and raise at least $1 billion to finance promising startups whic=
h, due to forces outside their own control, were strapped for cash.=E2=80=
=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At the time, I found this plan puzzling, becau=
se I had never heard of a crypto project that was =E2=80=9Cotherwise strong=
, but in a liquidity crisis.=E2=80=9D <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/32983479.262420/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGl=
uaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMTUvbWF0dC1sZXZpbmUtcy1tb25leS1zdHVmZi1iaW5hbm=
NlLWZ0eC1hbmQtY2Fycz9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMDEwMjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtY=
WlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzEwMTAmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1v=
bmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB923c8bbf" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" items=
cope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorati=
on: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000=
; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  I asked</a>:=C2=A0=
=E2=80=9CHas there ever been a pure liquidity problem at a crypto firm?=E2=
=80=9D Crypto project that got hacked and lost all its money? Sure. Crypto =
project whose founders ran off with all the money? Sure. Crypto project who=
se money was all in magic beans that turned out to be worthless? Sure.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But crypto project that had lots of good long-=
term assets that it could not sell or finance quickly, and that was therefo=
re driven into bankruptcy despite having lots of value? I mean? I suppose i=
t is still technically possible that <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/32983479.262420/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGlu=
aW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTAtMDUvZnR4LW1pZ2h0LWhhdmUtZm91bmQtc29tZS1tb25leT9=
jbXBpZD1CQkQxMDEwMjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bm=
V3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzEwMTAmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07cee=
f4b8524a319a23cC723b3438" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" ta=
rget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; =
border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style=
: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> that describes FTX</a>, but only by acci=
dent. (It gambled customer money on, among many worse things, a stake in ar=
tificial intelligence startup Anthropic that has gone up a lot in value sin=
ce FTX went bankrupt.) I just kind of do not think that that is how crypto=
=C2=A0<em>works</em>. Compared to traditional financial assets, crypto is u=
nusually good at being liquid (it all trades on computers around the clock)=
 but unusually bad at being solvent (it often turns out to be worthless). A=
 fund set up to solve liquidity problems in crypto won=E2=80=99t end up doi=
ng much.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Today Nicolle reports that Binance=E2=80=99s f=
und <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32983479.26242=
0/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTAtMTAvYmluY=
W5jZS1zLTEtYmlsbGlvbi1wbGFuLXRvLXNhdmUtY3J5cHRvLWFmdGVyLWZ0eC1oYXMtcXVpZXRs=
eS1maXp6bGVkLW91dD9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMDEwMjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWl=
sJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzEwMTAmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbm=
V5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cCb20e2c6c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsco=
pe=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration=
: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; =
border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">didn=E2=80=99t end up =
doing much</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Not much has come of Zhao=E2=80=99s grand plan=
 to rescue crypto. The Industry Recovery Initiative, as it was called, has =
deployed less than $30 million since its inception, a Bloomberg News analys=
is of public digital-asset wallets linked to the project indicates. Only on=
e of nine named participants has invested all the funds it committed. The c=
rypto asset sector, meanwhile, remains starved for cash and companies are c=
utting jobs to stay afloat.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The quiet unwinding of the IRI is a stark remi=
nder of crypto=E2=80=99s penchant for making bold promises it doesn=E2=80=
=99t always deliver on. It also echoes the much-diminished stature of Binan=
ce, which is facing lawsuits from two major US regulators, and of founders =
like Zhao, who once crisscrossed the world in private jets and mingled with=
 heads of state and celebrities. Bankman-Fried, who just months before FTX=
=E2=80=99s implosion had embarked on an industry bailout of his own, is now=
 on trial on fraud charges in New York.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t actually think that Zhao made =
any bold promises he didn=E2=80=99t deliver on? I think he promised to =E2=
=80=9Chelp projects who are otherwise strong, but in a liquidity crisis,=E2=
=80=9D and unsurprisingly there weren=E2=80=99t many.</p>
